doc.previous: The airport consists of three terminals with an overall number of 90 gates of which some are currently out of use Terminal A gates A1 A30 which all are currently out of use Terminal B gates B31 B60 and Terminal C gates C61 C90 SeaPort Airlines does not operate out of the main passenger terminal they use the private aviation terminal Kansas City closed Terminal A on January 8 2014 Kansas City is considering a plan to tear down Terminal A and build a new Central Terminal there but no formal announcement on that plan has been made yet 19
